{
  "text": "Hydroxyl concentrations and ionic activity in soil solutions may be increased by increasing pH as well as by Fe and Al precipitation. On the other hand, the precipitation of less-soluble P-Fe and P-Al compounds is reduced. Additionally, negative charges are generated by OH -deprotonation and are exposed by clays and organic matter. In this way, phosphate is repelled by the adsorption surface [CITATION_1] Pulz et al., 2008) , thereby releasing P into the soil solution. Thus, it was expected that both acidity correction materials would similarly increase P availability.",
